CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 29, 1965, pg. 9 reads: "Colorful Scene - This is just one of the sections where one could view the colorful scene brought about by the annual Garden Market of the Pittsburgh Garden Club Federation. Held at the Garden Center on Shady Ave., Oakland, the affair attracted large crowds on both days.
TitMainTitle: Men and women gathered at tents for the Garden Market sponsored by the Pittsburgh Garden Club Federation, at the Garden Center on Shady Avenue
